{"word":"G2165 - εὐφραίνω - euphraínō - yoo-frah'-ee-no - Fare","slug":"G2165","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐφραίνω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>euphraínō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yoo-frah'-ee-no"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Fare"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x03C5;&#x0313;&#x03C6;&#x03C1;&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03BD;&#x03C9; - euphraino&#x0304;</b> - <i>yoo-frah'ee-no</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G2095\">G2095</a> and <a href=\"#/G5424\">G5424</a>; to <i>put</i> (middle voice or passive voice <i>be</i>) <i>in a good</i> frame of <i>mind</i>, that is, <i>rejoice:</i> - fare, make glad, be (make) merry, rejoice."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2167\">G2167</a>"}]}